# Relay Module

## Overview

Relay Orchestrator executes serial agent flows with baton passing and gate enforcement

## Goals

- **G1** — Relay Orchestrator executes serial agent flows with baton passing and gate enforcement
- **G2** — Handoff Protocol compresses context between agents, achieving ~5× token savings vs parallel multi-agent
- **G3** — Live Relay Pipeline Visualization
- **G4** — Node-graph renders connected dots with animated handoff lines
- **G5** — Expanded node cards show real-time token burn and current action
- **G6** — Tester→Coder retry loop visualizes as backward edge with counter
- *...and 9 more*

## Key Architecture Decisions

- **A1** — Relay Orchestrator Architecture
- **A2** — Checkpoint & State Persistence
- **A3** — Boss-First Execution Architecture
- **A4** — Automatic Relay Mode Architecture
- **A5** — Cross-View Event Router Architecture

## Key Designs

- **D1** — PipelineEngine & Flow Execution
- **D2** — HandoffDocument Generation
- **D3** — Checkpoint Serialization
- **D4** — TokenBudget Enforcement
- **D5** — RelayMode & GSD Flow Control
- **D6** — useGateInbox State Machine
- **D7** — Relay PipelinePanel Node-Graph
- *...and 5 more*

